SUMMARY:Collection Spotlight Exhibit
DTSTAMP:20260326T024944Z
DTSTART:20260326T170000Z
DESCRIPTION:Thursday\, March 26\, 2026\, 10am - 6pm\n\nThis exhibit highlig
	hts the diversity and depth of The Seattle Public Library's collection\, c
	omposed of over two million items.\n\nLocation Link:\n\nCentral Library\n\
	nRoom Location: Level 8 - Gallery\n\nRegistration Required: Registration i
	s not required.\n\nDetailed Description: Enjoy viewing books\, ephemera\, 
	art\, and more at our exhibit in the Level 8 Gallery between January 23\, 
	2026 and April 11\, 2026.\, Thanks to our sponsor\n\nThe Seattle Public Li
	brary Foundation .\n\nEvent Logistics:\n\nFind out about Exhibits.\n\nCont
	act Us: If you have questions about this event\,\n\nAsk Us\n\nor call 206-
	386-4636.\n\nADA Accommodations: We can provide accommodations for people 
	with disabilities at Library events. Please\n\ncontactLEAP\n\nat least sev
	en days before the event to request accommodations.\, All Library programs
	 are free and open to the public.\,\n\nhttps://seatoday.6amcity.com/events
	/#/details/collection-spotlight-exhibit/18084351/2026-03-26T00\n\nFrom SEA
	today - Arts & Culture
